### 3. Three Dashboard Roles

| Role | Can See | Can Do |
|------|---------|--------|
| **Supervisor** | All departments, all issues, all stats | Reassign issues between depts, verify resolutions, view escalated issues, manage HODs |
| **Municipal** | Their department's issues only (highlighted first), city-wide map | Update status, upload resolution photo, add comments, see citizen contacts |
| **NGO** | All issues in their focus area | View issues, add supporting comments, showcase completed projects, track impact |

### 4. Deadline & Escalation System

```
Criticality → Deadline → Auto-escalation
─────────────────────────────────────────
🟢 Low      → 7 days  → escalate to supervisor
🟡 Medium   → 7 days  → escalate to supervisor  
🟠 High     → 3 days  → escalate to supervisor
🔴 Critical → 24 hrs  → escalate to supervisor
```

### 5. Urgency Score Algorithm
```
urgencyScore = (upvoteCount × 10) + (categoryWeight × 100) + deadlinePenalty

categoryWeight:
  - Water/Electricity issues = 1.5
  - Roads/Sanitation = 1.0
  - Parks = 0.8

deadlinePenalty:
  - > 50% deadline elapsed = +50
  - > 80% deadline elapsed = +100
  - Deadline exceeded = +200
```

### 6. Resolution Verification Flow

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant Muni as 🏛️ Municipal/HOD
    participant Sys as ⚡ System
    participant Sup as 👑 Supervisor
    participant Cit as 👤 Citizen

    Muni->>Sys: Upload resolution photo + note
    Sys->>Sys: Status: "pending_verification"
    Sys->>Cit: Notification: "Issue resolved - verify?"
    Sys->>Sup: Notification: "Resolution needs verification"
    
    alt Supervisor verifies
        Sup->>Sys: ✅ Tick - Confirmed resolved
        Sys->>Sys: Status: "resolved"
    else Citizen verifies
        Cit->>Sys: ✅ Tick - Confirmed resolved
        Sys->>Sys: Status: "resolved"
    else Rejected
        Sup->>Sys: ❌ Reject - Not resolved
        Sys->>Sys: Status: "in_progress" (reopened)
    end
```

